<comment datatype='string'>Expression levels of both &lt;i&gt;micC&lt;/i&gt; and &lt;i&gt;ompN&lt;/i&gt; are increased in the presence of -lactam antibiotics. On the other hand, under conditions when cells were depleted of &amp;sigma;&lt;sup&gt;E&lt;/sup&gt; upon overexpression of its cognate anti-sigma RseA, the activities of both &lt;i&gt;micC&lt;/i&gt; and the &lt;i&gt;ompN-lacZ&lt;/i&gt; fusion were affected. However, the &amp;sigma;&lt;sup&gt;E&lt;/sup&gt; core promoter motif was not found, which suggests an indirect effect [&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/29211019&quot;&gt;Dam17&lt;/a&gt;]. Finally, based on gene expression analysis, it was shown that H-NS could be regulating the expression of &lt;i&gt;micC&lt;/i&gt; and &lt;i&gt;ompN&lt;/i&gt; [&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/29211019&quot;&gt;Dam17&lt;/a&gt;].
&lt;p&gt;
MicC sRNA could be acting together with &amp;sigma;&lt;sup&gt;E&lt;/sup&gt; to control OmpC/N levels in response to -lactam antibiotics [&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/29211019&quot;&gt;Dam17&lt;/a&gt;].
&lt;p&gt;
The transcription of  the &lt;i&gt;ompN&lt;/i&gt; gene is induced during the first 24 h after the induction of nitrogen starvation [&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/32571968&quot;&gt;Switzer20&lt;/a&gt;].
</comment>
